00:52:51.520 --> 00:52:55.980
it's paying three
months LIBOR rate.

00:52:55.980 --> 00:52:57.500
And so this is
stochastic, right?

00:52:57.500 --> 00:53:02.550
So basically, every day, there
is this certain procedure,

00:53:02.550 --> 00:53:06.390
which tells us what this LIBOR,
this short-term borrowing rate

00:53:06.390 --> 00:53:08.580
is.

00:53:08.580 --> 00:53:11.030
And in exchange
for this, if you're

00:53:11.030 --> 00:53:14.000
paying out this LIBOR
swap, this LIBOR rate,

00:53:14.000 --> 00:53:16.634
you are receiving the fixed
rate, which is diminished.

00:53:16.634 --> 00:53:18.800
So this is like fundamental
interest rate basically.

00:53:18.800 --> 00:53:21.302
It's like, essentially, if you
believe that rates will go up

00:53:21.302 --> 00:53:23.010
and you just want to
speculate, basically

00:53:23.010 --> 00:53:25.780
you're trying to be long
LIBOR and short fixed rate,

00:53:25.780 --> 00:53:27.330
and vice versa.

00:53:27.330 --> 00:53:31.290
So this is a very important
instrument for pricing.

00:53:31.290 --> 00:53:33.420
And it's all kinds
of derivatives

00:53:33.420 --> 00:53:34.980
linked to this LIBOR rate.

00:53:34.980 --> 00:53:40.360
For example, you can
talk about a swaption.

00:53:40.360 --> 00:53:41.160
What is a swaption?

00:53:41.160 --> 00:53:44.450
Swaption is a derivative
to enter an interest rate

00:53:44.450 --> 00:53:46.192
swap in the future.

00:53:46.192 --> 00:53:47.900
Remember like in the
equity option world,

00:53:47.900 --> 00:53:51.110
let's say if I have a call
option on a stock, that's

00:53:51.110 --> 00:53:54.070
the right to buy
a stock at a fixed

00:53:54.070 --> 00:53:57.580
price-- it's fixed today-- like
at some time in the future.

00:53:57.580 --> 00:53:59.310
Here, this is basically
the same idea.

00:53:59.310 --> 00:54:02.140
If you're here today, at
sometime in the future

00:54:02.140 --> 00:54:03.980
you can enter a swap,
a kind of contract,

00:54:03.980 --> 00:54:07.450
which pays various
legs and there

00:54:07.450 --> 00:54:10.150
is some price given for today.

00:54:10.150 --> 00:54:13.600
And there are also all
kinds of false derivatives.

00:54:13.600 --> 00:54:15.490
You can talk about rates.

00:54:15.490 --> 00:54:20.080
Basically you can buy or sell
options on a particular LIBOR

00:54:20.080 --> 00:54:21.370
rate.

00:54:21.370 --> 00:54:23.730
Or there's also
cancel-able swaps,

00:54:23.730 --> 00:54:26.460
which basically are
you can enter a swap,

00:54:26.460 --> 00:54:29.490
but if you don't want to pay,
like, let's say, high rate

00:54:29.490 --> 00:54:30.690
anymore, you can cancel it.

00:54:30.690 --> 00:54:33.350
Of course, it's affecting
the price so on and so forth.

00:54:33.350 --> 00:54:36.700
So, very important idea if
you think about all these

00:54:36.700 --> 00:54:39.500
