price all these derivatives,

00:54:39.500 --> 00:54:45.280
they all depend-- Their price
depends on these discount

00:54:45.280 --> 00:54:46.550
factors.

00:54:46.550 --> 00:54:49.299
And the discount factors
depend on these forward rates,

00:54:49.299 --> 00:54:51.090
which is basically
trivial parametrization.

00:54:51.090 --> 00:54:53.915
But it's very important,
very convenient, to work

00:54:53.915 --> 00:54:55.380
with these forward rates.

00:54:55.380 --> 00:54:59.170
And when we model interest rate
derivatives, using Monte Carlo

00:54:59.170 --> 00:55:02.140
simulations, and there are no
