00:57:00.030 --> 00:57:03.360
The idea is very simple.

00:57:03.360 --> 00:57:05.460
So basically the
swap market allows

00:57:05.460 --> 00:57:10.970
you to obtain this
discount factor-- basically

00:57:10.970 --> 00:57:15.900
this function-- which tells
you how much your dollar

00:57:15.900 --> 00:57:19.530
in the future is today.

00:57:19.530 --> 00:57:21.400
So if you know how
much a dollar is,

00:57:21.400 --> 00:57:24.600
then you know how much C
dollars, basically, cost.

00:57:28.510 --> 00:57:30.490
Then basically, let's
say you have C dollars.

00:57:30.490 --> 00:57:33.380
Then you simply multiply
