an interest rate

00:59:07.877 --> 00:59:14.910
swap, which is paying LIBOR.

00:59:14.910 --> 00:59:17.060
And let's say on a notional.

00:59:17.060 --> 00:59:21.060
Let's say I pay you LIBOR,
which is some rate which

00:59:21.060 --> 00:59:22.910
is measured in percent.

00:59:22.910 --> 00:59:25.630
LIBOR is like a 1%
a year, for example.

00:59:25.630 --> 00:59:27.920
Then notional of the
swap is $1 million

00:59:27.920 --> 00:59:33.640
which means that the floating
rate payment is based on $1

00:59:33.640 --> 00:59:37.630
million times 1% is $10,000.

00:59:37.630 --> 00:59:40.880
So it turns out that
very interesting thing

00:59:40.880 --> 00:59:53.020
is that if you pay
LIBOR rate and if you

00:59:53.020 --> 00:59:55.010
pay the notional
at the very end,

00:59:55.010 --> 00:59:59.880
then the present value of
