01:00:35.292 --> 01:00:37.250
The main idea which you
need to understand here

01:00:37.250 --> 01:00:41.090
is that we have this function,
like discount function, which

01:00:41.090 --> 01:00:44.690
shows us again how much the
dollar is worth in the future.

01:00:44.690 --> 01:00:48.630
And using this function, we
can price all kinds of swaps.

01:00:48.630 --> 01:00:55.490
So we can PV the value of
the swap today using this.

01:00:55.490 --> 01:00:59.120
So the idea of interest
rate derivatives

01:00:59.120 --> 01:01:01.510
it's all about dynamics
of the yield curve.

01:01:01.510 --> 01:01:04.510
It's basically how
your discount function

01:01:04.510 --> 01:01:10.480
or how your yields,
future yields, evolve.

01:01:10.480 --> 01:01:14.100
The whole idea is
similar to the stock.

01:01:14.100 --> 01:01:20.640
So again, at time 0 you
